  "market_context": "Daily chart showed a reversal candle closing back inside the prior day's range, indicating failed bearish continuation. Hourly chart confirmed with a V-shaped reversal and SMT divergence against YM1, setting up a bullish continuation bias for the day.",
  "key_observation": "A daily reversal candle was followed by a V-shaped reversal on the hourly timeframe, with SMT confirmation between ES1! and YM1, enabling a high-probability long entry on closure through down-close candles targeting buy-side liquidity at 2R.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified a daily reversal candle on ES1! that closed back inside the previous day’s range, signaling failure of bearish continuation and potential bullish reversal.",
    "Step 2: On the hourly timeframe, analyst observed a V-shaped reversal pattern forming after a sweep of short-term liquidity, confirming the reversal structure.",
    "Step 3: Analyst noted an SMT (Smart Money Technique) divergence between ES1! and YM1, where ES1! made a higher low while YM1 made a lower low, validating the reversal and relative strength.",
    "Step 4: Analyst waited for a closure through the series of down-close candles that formed the hourly swing low, identifying this as the change in state of delivery and entry trigger.",
    "Step 5: Entry was taken with stop below the swing low, targeting buy-side liquidity (equal highs) where 2R risk-to-reward was achievable."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit 2R target at buy-side liquidity; also noted RTP (risk-to-reward target) was achieved. A second SMT formed with YM during the move.",
  "lessons": "Daily reversals require lower-time-frame confirmation via protected swing formation and SMT. Continuation entries after reversal are highest probability when aligned across timeframes and supported by intermarket divergence.",
